The local development workflow in `shared/python.mk` now uses `uv sync --all-extras` to install **all** optional dependencies (`dev`, `gpu`, `compute`, `vault-health`, `finetune`) in a single command. This eliminates the `missing_extra` error when importing from HuggingFace Hub and ensures GPU, Modal compute, and vault health checks work out of the box.

## Why this matters

Previously, `make setup` only installed `--extra dev` (plus conditional `--extra gpu`). The `[finetune]` extra (huggingface_hub, transformers, tokenizers, peft, bitsandbytes, etc.) was absent by default, causing import jobs to fail with a `missing_extra` error. Developers had to manually run `uv sync --extra finetune` as a separate step.

The switch to `--all-extras` is the simplest, most boring solution: for local development, installing everything is the right default. No one benefits from a lean venv during development, and the optional extras are small compared to the cost of debugging missing dependencies.

